cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses security issues in shared hosting and proposes methods to handle them.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the administration and management of websites in shared hosting.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as shared hosting involves multiple websites residing on one webserver.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of different methods for shared hosting security.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the evaluation of different methods for shared hosting security.
